---

## 📖 About

**V.A.U.L.T** (Virtualized Automated Utility & Logic Tool) is a collection of experimental projects and iterations  
aimed at building a **Jarvis-like assistant** for automation, productivity, and experimentation.  

Each iteration (`MARK2`, `MARK3`, … `MARK9`) represents improvements and new features — from simple scripts  
to more complex AI-assisted workflows.

---

## 🚀 Features
- Modular design — projects separated by MARK versions
- Automation scripts (job applications, productivity tools, system helpers)
- AI-enhanced experiments
- Scalable structure for future iterations

---

## 📂 Project Structure
```
V.A.U.L.T/
├─ V.A.U.L.T MK2
├─ V.A.U.L.T MK3
├─ V.A.U.L.T MARK4
├─ V.A.U.L.T MARK5
├─ V.A.U.L.T MARK6
├─ V.A.U.L.T MARK7
├─ V.A.U.L.T MARK8
├─ V.A.U.L.T MARK9
├─ JARVIS PROJESI
├─ VAULT PROJESI
└─ Otomatik iş başvuru
```

> Each MARK folder contains a different iteration of the project.  
> Future releases will unify these into a more cohesive assistant.

---

## 🛠️ Technologies
- **Languages:** Python, JavaScript, HTML, CSS
- **Tools:** GitHub Pages, Node.js (optional), CLI automation
- **Extras:** Shields.io badges, modular configs

---

## 📦 Getting Started
Clone the repository and explore any MARK iteration:

```bash
git clone https://github.com/kutaykilicai/V.A.U.L.T.git
cd V.A.U.L.T
```

To run an iteration (example for `Otomatik iş başvuru`):
```bash
cd "Otomatik iş başvuru"
python main.py --help
```

